<div class="sect4">
<h5 id="130">Preparing the import file</h5>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Now you can prepare the CSV file containing your item data. Download the sample CSV file and familiarise yourself with the file structure.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>If you want to import a lot of item data at once, then before you start the import, make sure you have saved all the data in your system that you will need to link items and variations:</p>
</div>
<div class="ulist">
<ul>
<li>
<p>Categories</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Attributes</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Sales prices</p>
</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect4">
<h5 id="140">Creating a sync for the initial item import</h5>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>In plentymarkets, you import data using ElasticSync. First, you create a sync, then you map the fields you want to import data into in plentymarkets.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Creating a sync for the item import:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Data » ElasticSync</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Add sync</strong>.<br>
→ The editing area <strong>New sync</strong> is displayed.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Enter <strong>Initial item import</strong> into the <strong>Name</strong> field.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Select <strong>Item</strong> from the <strong>Type</strong> drop-down list.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Carry out the settings in the <strong>Import</strong> section. Pay attention to the information in &lt;table-create-sync&gt;.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Select <strong>HTTP</strong> from the <strong>Source</strong> drop-down list.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Select <strong>Data upload</strong> from the <strong>HTTP options</strong> drop-down list.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the More icon in the <strong>URL</strong> field.<br></p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Upload file</strong> in the overlay.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Use the folder navigation to select the file you want to import.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Open</strong>.<br>
→ The file is uploaded.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the file in the list to select it.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Select</strong>.<br>
<strong><em>Tip:</em></strong> If the button is greyed out, click on the file in the list.<br>
→ The file is flagged for import.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> the settings.<br>
→ The sync is created.<br>
→ The matching settings of the sync open.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
